entry.title: No longer hearing audio when using Chrome
entry.content:
# Steps to reproduce the problem 1. Open chrome 2. Click to listen to audio on any website containing audio 3.
# Problem Description I have a Universal Audio Apollo as my main interface and I've had no issues playing back sound from various apps and web browsers for years; but all of a sudden yesterday, after I woke my computer from sleep, I can no longer get any sound whenever I play audio in Google Chrome.
I can hear audio from all other apps and browsers still. It is only Chrome that is affected.
I've tried updating Chrome, my UA software, powering on/off my interface and computer, clearing cache, and making sure I didn't have any settings in Chrome that muted audio... I've tried a bunch of things, yet still no audio.
If I disconnect my Apollo from my computer, I can hear music from Chrome on my computer's speakers with no problem. So I suspect that it's how Chrome interacts with the Apollo.
# Summary No longer hearing audio when using Chrome
# Custom Questions #### Does this work in other browsers?
Yes - This is just a Chromium problem
